        con't.d...couldn't stop with just 10 80s classics :))))  we had too many hits that decade!

         11. olivia newton-john & cliff richard/suddenly *early 1981-US*: https://www.youtube.c*m/watch?v=qT_xpgdEjJE over here, before this single, she was more known for love ballads and her role as sandy in 'grease'.  this was off the xanadu soundtrack & i remember my parents had this one and her hugely successful 'physical' album during this time.  hard to believe this song only peaked @ #20 on the hot 100!  but don't worry, she would later have a then-record breaking #1 smash with 'physical' @ 10 wks @ #1.  but this song perfectly showcases her beautiful voice!

        12. sheila e./the glamorous life *1984*: https://www.youtube.c*m/watch?v=HpO07s-Aw4I prince did this one and it peaked @ #7 on the hot 100 *prince was HUGE that year in america with his iconic 'purple rain soundtrack'*.  i can't recall anything more from her, but we had one hit after another all throughout the 80s. 

        13. nu shooz/i can't wait *1986* : https://www.youtube.c*m/watch?v=KdPfy1Khjpg peaking @ #3 on the hot 100 chart, they're a married couple *still happily married today!* & this song perfectly showcases how eclectic and diverse the 80s music scene really was.  not a traditional pop or club song, very unique for the times.  

        14. the carpenters/touch me when we're dancing *1981*: https://www.youtube.c*m/watch?v=55uJ3lfNJE8 the carpenters were a brother/sister duo who were big worldwide and over here were a pop phenomenon notching top 10 hit after another mostly in the 70s.  sadly karen passed away in 1983 BUT had 1 of the most beautiful voices you'll ever hear!  i highly recommend everyone check out more of the carpenters music!  they were one of best musical acts of all time :)))))  & believe it or not, karen was best friends with olivia newton john during this time. 

        15. scandal/the warrior *1984*: https://www.youtube.c*m/watch?v=yMHtDFDJCqY peaking @ #7 over here, i can only recall 1 other hit from them 'goodbye to you'...but when you turned on the radio here in america you would listen to 1 great song after another.  

        see how awesome the 80s music scene was?  hard to just pick 10 LOL!  i'll do a 90s list next time with some not so familiar, but some good ones i think you all will like :)))))

        cont'd...sorry mates, wanted to break up my list...

        6. foreigner/waiting for a girl like you *1981*: https://www.youtube.c*m/watch?v=RIdfPBmUAXc peaked @ #2 for a record-breaking 10 wks @ the #2 spot on the hot 100 chart *missy elliot's 'work it' tied them for 10 wks @ #2 stuck behind eminem's 'lose yourself'.  he was #1 for 10 straight wks!  lots of fun being a hot 100 fan*.  robert john 'mutt' lange also did this album...an 80s classic right here! 

        7.  robert palmer/addicted to love *1986*: https://www.youtube.c*m/watch?v=vBPmyXyW6yk&list=PLbGuJX1GQkocvNiq8XU_3Ug5sFlverOe1&index=3 this vid was hugely popular on mtv here and would top the hot 100 chart.  he did very well here notching a handful of top 10 hits on the billboard hot 100 chart...and sadly he passed away in 2003.  

        8. kix/don't close your eyes *1988*: https://www.youtube.c*m/watch?v=5mvogEVDaJg  during this time here in america we had a TON of rock bands with just one rock hit after another.  peaked @ #11 on the hot 100 chart and it dealt with suicide, very controversial back then.  but sounded great on the radio!  

        9. debbie gibson/out of the blue *1987* https://www.youtube.c*m/watch?v=7FribHKQSIc : teen pop artist who i idolized back then!!  she would later be the youngest artist to write, produce and sing a #1 hit on the hot 100 chart with her #1 hit 'foolish beat' (later in the year)  this album is still a great 80s pop album to listen to.  

        10. pretty poison/catch me i'm falling *1987* : https://www.youtube.c*m/watch?v=3Z76XfRklLk  in the 80s over here we not only had artists go to great heights, but we also had artists that might've have just 1 or less than 5 hits *very hard to compete against big artists like michael jackson, whitney, madonna, janet, prince, etc.* but where even that 1 hit would be a big smash!  i can't recall anything else from them, but this single peaked @#8 on the hot 100...loved it on the radio back then.

        1 thing about growing up in the 80s, we had NOTHING but great music :))))).  so here's a list of 80s tracks that you all might not be too familiar with & lesser known tracks from huge artists, but they all sound just as good today as they all did back then...enjoy everyone!  

        1. inxs/need you tonight *1987*: https://www.youtube.c*m/watch?v=Swdbv5I6qzc this was their lead single off their fantastic 'kick' album here in america...it did very well, 6x plat. & 4 huge top 10 hits.  'need you tonight' would top the billboard hot 100 chart during this time.  

        2. heart/never *1985*: https://www.youtube.c*m/watch?v=xCEFysCT1a4 this album would go 5x plat. and yield 4 top 10 hits.  i was 10 yrs old this year and madonna's like a virgin album & the 'we are the world' single would be so big, so any artist that could compete with them is extraordinary.

        3. madonna/love don't live here anymore *1984*: https://www.youtube.c*m/watch?v=-oKl_4p-4Hcoff the huge 'like a virgin' album, not a big hit over here at the time *but don't worry, she racked up huge top 10 hits & #1 smashes during this time* but 1 of her very best tracks.  throughout the 80s & 90s she had 1 big hit after another and another.  i still love this album today!

        4. the cars/magic *1984*: https://www.youtube.c*m/watch?v=B1f0VRdM4BM robert john 'mutt' lange *famous for producing def leppard & shania twain* produced the cars amazing 'heartbeat city' album.  i was too young to get into the cars during this time, but over here they were constantly on mtv & on the radio.  i highly recommend everyone check out their amazing 'heartbeat city' album!!  1 of the best albums to come from the 80s.  

        5. george michael & aretha franklin/i knew you were waiting for me *1987*: https://www.youtube.c*m/watch?v=B1f0VRdM4BM  came out in early 1987 and would peak @ #1 on the hot 100 chart.  during this time george hadn't become a big solo artist over here quite yet *don't worry, that would change by the end of the year ;)*  later in the summer of this year george michael would blow up here in america & be right up there with the top selling u.s. artists like michael jackson, madonna, whitney houston, prince, bon jovi.
